OLYMPIA, Wash. (AP) â€” The office of a Republican Washington state lawmaker was vandalized by two people who smashed a window before tossing a lit flare inside.House Republican Leader J.T. Wilcox posted Ring video footage to Twitter that showed the individuals approach the building around 4 a.m. Monday. Both had their faces covered, and one smashed the window with a hammer before the other dropped the flare into the building, The Olympian reported.Wilcox says the building, which also houses House Republican campaign offices, is fine because the flare landed on a masonry floor. The incident has been reported to both Olympia Police and the Washington State Patrol.